  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi words 'Shubh' and 'Laabh'?",
  "response": "The Hindi words \"Shubh\" and \"Laabh\" have the following meanings:\n\n*   **Shubh (\u0936\u0941\u092d):** Means auspicious, good, or beneficial. It signifies something that brings good fortune, positivity, and well-being.\n\n*   **Laabh (\u0932\u093e\u092d):** Means profit, gain, benefit, or advantage. It represents a financial or material gain, as well as any kind of benefit derived from an action or situation.\n\nIn Hindi culture, these words are often written together as **\"Shubh Laabh\" (\u0936\u0941\u092d \u0932\u093e\u092d)**, symbolizing the wish for both auspiciousness and prosperity. It is common to see this phrase inscribed during religious ceremonies, on doorways of homes and businesses, and on items associated with wealth and good fortune, like account books or safes.",
